The article commemorates the Meds Yeghern, a mass atrocity during which one and a half million Armenians were deported, massacred, or marched to their deaths in the final years of the Ottoman Empire. The article expresses grief for the lives lost and acknowledges the courage of those who sought to end the violence and aid survivors. It also recognizes the resilience of the Armenian people and their contributions to the United States. The article emphasizes the importance of acknowledging and reckoning with the past to create a more tolerant future. It concludes by standing with the Armenian people and committing to work together for a better future.